BAUCHI  – No fewer than 20 persons were burnt beyond recognition on Sunday in a fatal auto-crash that occuredat Mangororiin Tirwun village, which is 3km away from Bauchi metropolis. Daily Independent learnt that the accident in volveda Hummer Bus belonging to Borno Express, which was heading to Maiduguri from Jos with 18 passengers and a VW Golf vehicle coming from Misau and heading to Bauchi with four passengers. According to an eyewitness account, the accident was caused as a result of a head-on collision, which made the two vehicles go up in flames. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The eyewitness said the pas­sengers were burnt beyond rec­ognition after a combined team of firefighters from Bauchi put off the fire, in the end, two fe­male passengers survived with degrees of injuries. Confirming the incidence, the Bauchi State Police Command through its PPRO, DSP Ahmed Wakili, said that the charred bod­ies of the victims have been de­posited at the mortuary of Abu­bakar Tafawa Balewa University Teaching Hospital (ATBUTH) while the two female survivors were receiving treatment at the same hospital.